<h4 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="22f83616-5709-47cf-a0f5-6f6dac76c531" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="56">Yes—<strong data-start="4" data-end="26">with one condition</strong>, and I’ll be honest with you.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="1nnzc0f" data-start="58" data-end="91">👍 What you’re doing right now</h2>
<p data-start="92" data-end="100">You are:</p>
<ul data-start="101" data-end="182">
<li data-section-id="hbpp55" data-start="101" data-end="130">
<p data-start="103" data-end="130">Writing the code yourself</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="rhz8mu" data-start="131" data-end="164">
<p data-start="133" data-end="164">Asking <em data-start="140" data-end="162">why each line exists</em></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="kdmjck" data-start="165" data-end="182">
<p data-start="167" data-end="182">Fixing errors</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="184" data-end="243">👉 This is <strong data-start="195" data-end="217">effective learning</strong>. You’re not just copying.</p>
<hr data-start="245" data-end="248">
<h2 data-section-id="19mrpln" data-start="250" data-end="286">⚠️ But here’s the important catch</h2>
<p data-start="288" data-end="340">If you only <strong data-start="300" data-end="319">type what I say</strong>, it becomes passive.</p>
<p data-start="342" data-end="392">To make it truly effective, you must add one step:</p>
<hr data-start="394" data-end="397">
<h2 data-section-id="3vrt3p" data-start="399" data-end="443">🔥 The correct learning method (use this)</h2>
<h3 data-section-id="psa1cd" data-start="445" data-end="495">Step 1: Write the code (what you’re doing now)</h3>
<p data-start="496" data-end="503">Good 👍</p>
<h3 data-section-id="127y888" data-start="505" data-end="554">Step 2: Stop and explain it in your own words</h3>
<p data-start="555" data-end="563">Example:</p>
<blockquote data-start="564" data-end="644">
<p data-start="566" data-end="644">“This line moves the uploaded file from temporary location to uploads folder.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="646" data-end="681">If you can explain → you understand</p>
<hr data-start="683" data-end="686">
<h3 data-section-id="131anjf" data-start="688" data-end="728">Step 3: Close everything and rewrite</h3>
<p data-start="730" data-end="776">After finishing a feature (like image upload):</p>
<p data-start="778" data-end="855">👉 Close VS Code<br data-start="794" data-end="797">
👉 Open new file<br data-start="813" data-end="816">
👉 Try to write it again without help</p>
<hr data-start="857" data-end="860">
<h2 data-section-id="g8qww3" data-start="862" data-end="881">🧠 Reality check</h2>
<p data-start="883" data-end="905">If you cannot rewrite:</p>
<p data-start="907" data-end="954">👉 You <strong data-start="914" data-end="937">learned temporarily</strong>, not permanently</p>
<hr data-start="956" data-end="959">
<h2 data-section-id="1di3ueh" data-start="961" data-end="995">🎯 What interviewers care about</h2>
<p data-start="997" data-end="1001">Not:</p>
